# Tailwind CSS & UI Style Guide

## Layout & Responsiveness
- **Mobile-First Prep:** Phase 1 is a web MVP, but it will eventually transition to React Native. Build dashboards and forms using clean, responsive Tailwind layouts (`flex`, `grid`, `md:grid-cols-2`) so the viewport scales gracefully down to mobile screens.
- Use strict flexbox spacing (`space-y-4`, `gap-6`) instead of arbitrary margins.

## Interactive Forms (Data Entry)
- Data entry forms for recording fairways, GIR, and putts must be clean, large, and tap-friendly (anticipating future mobile use).
- Use distinct visual states for miss direction toggles (e.g., a 3-button toggle group for Off-the-Tee: [ Left | Hit | Right ]).